Step 1: git init

Step 2: git config --global user.name 'Aman Sharma'

Step 3: git config --global user.email 'aman.sharma9645@gmail.com'

Step 4: touch index.html

Step 5: git add index.html

Step 6: git status

To remove file from staging area:
git rm --cached index.html

Make Changes to files and then again git status
You get modified for file you made changes to 

To add modified file in staging area do step 8

Step 8: git add . 

Step 9: git commit
It will open vim terminal or maybe normal file
 Remove # from initial commit in file
 Ctrl + X and y

 Step 10: modify the file and then do

 git commit -m 'changed app.js'


Step 11: Use gitignore 
        >>> touch .gitignore

Step 12: Add files to gitignore that you don't want to be added

log.txt
/dir2 (for directories use /)


Step 13: Use the concept of branching in Git to avoid direct modifications to master branch

Note: Always commit to master and then create a branch

Create a branch using 
>>> git branch login (upto you what name you choose)

Step 14: Switch into branch 

>>> git checkout login

Step 15: Switch back to master

>>> git checkout master